node.text:
.
asked me in a comment if I had a timeline of my fitness journey and I didn’t. So I took the time to do one for all you who follow me and support me. 

Now I try to be as transparent as possible when it comes down to my fitness. This week alone I’ve been getting so many backlash about how I didn’t lose this naturally and how it was impossible. So many disgusting comments and people writing to me in my DM saying that I’m a FRAUD”! I don’t know what makes people think that I am or have them the idea.

Yes I was wearing disposable garments that appear to be the ones people wear when under going surgeries, I had no idea. I went to get a sauna session. Some people said that I wasn’t truthful with my results, nobody here knows me like that personally besides my family and close friends. Y’all decided to follow me because you see some REAL RESULTS! I never faked anything. I’m a real genuine person with a great heart and care for people. 

I tried my best to make this video for those who are losing hope and are struggling forreal.  Get DMs about people who are not mentally in the right state of mind, depressed.

You may not know but I was depressed when I started. I was down I was sad I didn’t love myself, I wanted to eliminate myself from this world. I tried, but my God my Lord and Savior gave me strength and I prayed every day to Him crying to help me. 

I didn’t feel good about myself at all I was the biggest one in my family. Nobody in my family is fat or big. It doesn’t even run in our family. When I gained weight I was in a very tough spot. I was in a relationship that was mentally & emotionally abusive. I was drinking my life away I became an alcoholic and drank my feelings away and the pain I ensured. 

I would go to stores to try things in in H&M and they didn’t fit. I had holes in my pants cause my thighs rubbed together. I was disgusted with myself cause I’d how let myself go so carelessly. Then to hear people say here that I had SURGERY is sooo freaking misleading and absurd.

My story is long, so long I could write a book about it. (One day)

This video represents me! 

I hope I gave you some hope ❤️

node.text:
👉 Follow @bodysmartfitness for the best mindset, nutrition and fitness tips 
 
👉  Follow @bodysmartfitness 
 
The team at @bodysmartfitness want you to know the truth about diets, nutrition, food, fitness and the mindset hacks that will ensure your success. 
 
😀 We all want to feel good. 
 
😀 We all want to feel happy. 
 
⭐️ We all want to be a success (however success looks for us). 
 
@Bodysmartfitness blend a powerful trilogy of mindset, nutrition and fitness education to help people stop being stuck in a yo-yo cycle of fads and frustration. 
 
🌎 Founded by Jaymie Moran and with a global team of online coaches in the UK, America and Australia, the team coach women to get sustainable results for life without giving up the foods they love. 
 
💬 Jaymie said, "We wanted to start the Body Smart Fitness YouTube channel to give even more people the right science-backed information, inspiration and tools to create lasting results. Basically, we want to give you the TRUTH." 
 
💬 "Nothing gets me more annoyed and frustrated than people remaining stuck in a trap of yo-yo diets and ineffective exercise for years, coupled with a mindset that has been shaped by you thinking you're a failure every time you try and fail a diet. You're not a failure, you have been lied to." 
 
😥 "The diet industry keeps you trapped. My team and I are here to help you break free from that trap." 
 
💪 "Because losing weight is the easy part." 
 
🤯 "It is keeping it off that is hard." 
 
👉 Access @bodysmartfitness YouTube channel via the link in bio. Don't forget to subscribe and click the notification bell so you get first access to the videos. 
 
Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness 
Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness 
 Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness

node.text:
.
.
To get rid of fat deposits on your back, you’ll need to start by creating a caloric deficit. That means that you’ll need to burn more calories during the day than you consume.

In addition to cutting calories, you’ll get rid of back fat more quickly if you focus your exercise routine to target the muscles in your upper and lower back.

Adding high-intensity interval exercise (HIIT) to your routine, along with working out these specific muscles, will start to give you the results that you’re looking for. 
.
.
By @fitonomyapp

#quarentreino em casa tbm da pra chorar 😅💪🏽 ·

1- Agachamento peso corporal 
Realizar 3x series dessa sequência c/ 30seg descanso por série 
30rep completas +
30rep curtas +
30seg isometria 
2- 3x series dessa sequência - 30 seg descanso por série 
Afundo +Agachamento+ Isometria- A cada passada para cada lado (total de 10 para cada perna) realiza 5 agachamentos em movimento acelerado , no final , 1 min de isometria ( costas na parede)

3- Agachamento Búlgaro ( pés apoiado na cadeira/ banco/ sofá ) 4x15rep cada lado sem descanso 
4- Elevação de quadril unilateral ( tronco apoiado na cadeira/banco/ sofá) 4x20rep cada lado sem descanso 
5 - 4 apoios ( realizar os movimentos cadência lenta ) 3xseries para cada lado - 10seg de descanso ao final de cada série 
15 rep - joelhos em extensão .+
15rep - joelhos flexionados 
6- Panturrilhas ( utilizar um degrau ou apoio)
5x30seg de execução ( total amplitude ) - 15 seg descanso
.
.
.

Full Leg Day Killer 🔥💪

Treino de MMI com 01. Agachamento máquina 15/12/10 + drop com extensora 4 x 4 / 4x3 / 4x2 /4x 1 aumentando a carga ( 1 série ) 
1 x 10 com pico de contração em cima + 10 saindo da inércia 
1 x 10 com excêntrica lenta + 10 concêntrica lenta + 10 
02. Stiff 3 x 15 + bom dia 10 
03. Flexora 9 x 6 alternando a carga entre leva e pesado 
1 x 30 curtas + 10 isometria + 12 
1 x unilateral 8 /7/6 até zerar sem intervalo 
04. Flexora em pé 3 x 12 parando no meio + glúteo no cabo 3 x 12 
Panturrilhas sempre 😅
Macacão @santtaloren

.

node.text:
You have tried hating your body. You know that doesn’t work. So what if, today, tomorrow, what if you tried respecting it instead? 
⠀⠀⠀
Not ‘loving’ it. 
Not grabbing fistfuls of what feels shameful or delicate and screaming that it’s the most glorious thing in the world. 
⠀⠀⠀
But respecting it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
Respecting your thighs for how they let you move. 
Your arms for the hugs they hold. 
Your legs for their dance, their jumps. 
⠀⠀⠀
Honouring your tummy for the food it turns to fuel,
Your smile for the lives it has nurtured,
The hearts it has filled. 
⠀⠀⠀
What would that feel like? 
⠀⠀⠀
I can’t answer for you,
But I’ve got a pretty good guess:
⠀⠀⠀
That, that type of self respect, even at its most delicate, 
Would feel magical. 
Powerful. 
Incredible.
⠀⠀⠀
It would feel like coming home. 
⠀⠀⠀

@jbauerfit is looking for 5 busy professionals that want to lose 20-40 lbs quickly while eating their favorite foods & create a sustainable lifestyle they love!

Follow 👉 @jbauerfit to learn how to transform your body and life WITHOUT the restrictions or intensity.

So many people will cut carbs, train like maniacs, hop from program to program in search of that thing to actually “stick”...

Then get frustrated, burnt out, and start wondering if it’s even possible to see fitness results...

Here’s the truth… There are a few small and unique fitness and nutrition adjustments that lead to MASSIVE fitness results…

@Jbauerfit promotes a flexible, easy-to-follow approach with his clients who are getting incredible, SUSTAINED results week after week with a tight schedule and no desire to “diet”.

You will be implementing a proven system that has helped hundreds of people who have collectively lost several thousands of pounds.

So if you’re feeling stuck, unsure of what to do, or like there’s something “missing” on your fitness journey, message @Jbauerfit with #READY to chat 1v1 about your goals and see how to make your transformation happen in record time.

node.text:
CHECK IN TUESDAY - SEP 2020 - MAY 2021 - SEP 2021 #gainwithmilly 💪🏼

(Before diving in, how much you weigh DOES NOT DEFINE YOU!!! These numbers are here to show you not to be scared of being a heavier weight. I was SO much confident at my heaviest. So much happier and SO much healthier)

She’s back with another check in! Guys it’s nearly been a whole year since I started gaining weight 🥺 where has the time gone?!?🤯 

As I’m on mission “let’s reveal some of this muscle”, I’ve got lots of questions about whether my period has disappeared again, and I can happily say she hasn’t ☺️ it still isn’t entirely predictable, but I reckon that’s standard given I lost my period for a 8 years straight 🥲 (I’m not a doctor) 

I’ve been very very social recently (and still have a lot more social events coming up), so there’s been times I’ve felt more bloated than normal, which is still perfectly fine and should neverrrr outweigh the fun and memories that are made. Sometimes I can’t fit in my workouts from my programme in the week, and that’s still ok. Sometimes I have more indulging days than ‘normal’ and that’s ok. That’s life, and I love it that way☺️ 

I’m here to show you that you don’t ‘lose all of your progress’ when you live your balanced life. Sometimes you have to look back on where you started and see truly how far you have come (whether that’s by a lot or a little). You have to tell yourself that YOU DID THAT! 

I look at these pics and tell myself I DID THAT!!? I did that and it’s mental to realise that I’ve flipped my life around in only just a year. 

This week I’m having pizza with friends, off to a pretty coool after party and also a festival. Last week I was at more events, and I went away for the weekend with lots of food and alcohol. I’m not compensating ANYTHING. I’m not changing any behaviours. I’m just living and riding the wave 🌊 surfing allll of those narly waves like a queen and so should you 🤪
cc: @millyg_fit

node.text:
Follow 👉 @Dr.Stefan.Gospodinov for the best Nutrition, Fitness & Mindset tips!
.
When I started my fitness journey I swear EVERYONE had their opinions of me - how I looked, how I worked out or what I ate 🙃 I was never ‘skinny’ but people always would say things like “why are you on a diet?” Or “why do you workout so much?” 💭 They always tried to tempt me or tease me with certain foods & if anything, I just found it annoying 😅 Not helpful. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
People can be so judgemental of others. Even Mum said she thought I was “too muscly” once 🙈 She's a cutie! Others used to say that I didn’t “have abs” even though I worked out so hard... lol I was in uni, no one I knew had abs & no one knew if I did or didn't 😂 ⁣
⁣
BUT it is so important to do what is best for you! I have been reflecting a lot on my childhood & how I was teased which impacts how I feel now - I always assume people are negatively judging me which can be so tough mentally 😭 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Starting a fitness journey can be REALLY hard if you don’t have people on the same path to support & encourage you: I know - I’ve been there 💯 Even though your family means well by trying to feed you all the yummy food, it doesn’t mean that it helps you achieve your goals. Especially if you are overweight and are looking to lose fat in order to live a happy, healthy & long life ✔️⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
1️⃣You need to be clear of your goals. Write down WHY you want to be on this journey. The WHY needs to be so strong that you can stand up for yourself & politely express that you know what is best for you 💯⁣⁣⁣
2️⃣Find a friend/family member/partner to support you or join an online support group & follow others that are on the same journey as you ⁣⁣⁣
3️⃣ Know that not everyone will understand you goals, it’s not their job to. Sometimes you just need to be your own cheerleader!! You’ve got this!! ⁣⁣🤩⁣
⁣⁣⁣
LEFT: weight training for a few years, partying/traveling, uni lifestyle. 
RIGHT: comp prep, consistent, tracking macros, weight training 🔥 
⁣
.
.
.
Credit @anjuli_fitforlife #abworkout #coreworkout #quadsworkout #
